38Reader::Reader(const DecodeHints& hints) :
39 _tryHarder(hints.tryHarder()),
40 _tryRotate(hints.tryRotate())
41{
42 _readers.reserve(8);
43
44 if (hints.hasNoFormat()) {
45 _readers.emplace_back(new MultiUPCEANReader(hints));
46 _readers.emplace_back(new Code39Reader(hints));
47 _readers.emplace_back(new CodabarReader(hints));
48 _readers.emplace_back(new Code93Reader());
49 _readers.emplace_back(new Code128Reader(hints));
50 _readers.emplace_back(new ITFReader(hints));
51 _readers.emplace_back(new RSS14Reader());
52 _readers.emplace_back(new RSSExpandedReader());
53 }
54 else {
55 if (hints.hasFormat(BarcodeFormat::EAN_13) ||
56 hints.hasFormat(BarcodeFormat::UPC_A) ||
57 hints.hasFormat(BarcodeFormat::EAN_8) ||
58 hints.hasFormat(BarcodeFormat::UPC_E)) {
59 _readers.emplace_back(new MultiUPCEANReader(hints));
60 }
61 if (hints.hasFormat(BarcodeFormat::CODE_39)) {
62 _readers.emplace_back(new Code39Reader(hints));
63 }
64 if (hints.hasFormat(BarcodeFormat::CODE_93)) {
65 _readers.emplace_back(new Code93Reader());
66 }
67 if (hints.hasFormat(BarcodeFormat::CODE_128)) {
68 _readers.emplace_back(new Code128Reader(hints));
69 }
70 if (hints.hasFormat(BarcodeFormat::ITF)) {
71 _readers.emplace_back(new ITFReader(hints));
72 }
73 if (hints.hasFormat(BarcodeFormat::CODABAR)) {
74 _readers.emplace_back(new CodabarReader(hints));
75 }
76 if (hints.hasFormat(BarcodeFormat::RSS_14)) {
77 _readers.emplace_back(new RSS14Reader());
78 }
79 if (hints.hasFormat(BarcodeFormat::RSS_EXPANDED)) {
80 _readers.emplace_back(new RSSExpandedReader());
81 }
82 }
83}
84
85Reader::~Reader() = default;
86
87/**
88* We're going to examine rows from the middle outward, searching alternately above and below the
89* middle, and farther out each time. rowStep is the number of rows between each successive
90* attempt above and below the middle. So we'd scan row middle, then middle - rowStep, then
91* middle + rowStep, then middle - (2 * rowStep), etc.
92* rowStep is bigger as the image is taller, but is always at least 1. We've somewhat arbitrarily
93* decided that moving up and down by about 1/16 of the image is pretty good; we try more of the
94* image if "trying harder".
95*
96* @param image The image to decode
97* @param hints Any hints that were requested
98* @return The contents of the decoded barcode
99* @throws NotFoundException Any spontaneous errors which occur
100*/
101static Result
102DoDecode(const std::vector<std::unique_ptr<RowReader>>& readers, const BinaryBitmap& image, bool tryHarder)
103{
104 std::vector<std::unique_ptr<RowReader::DecodingState>> decodingState(readers.size());
105
106 int width = image.width();
107 int height = image.height();
108
109 int middle = height >> 1;
110 int rowStep = std::max(1, height >> (tryHarder ? 8 : 5));
111 int maxLines = tryHarder ?
112 height : // Look at the whole image, not just the center
113 15; // 15 rows spaced 1/32 apart is roughly the middle half of the image
114
115 BitArray row(width);
116#ifdef ZX_USE_NEW_ROW_READERS
117 PatternRow bars;
118 bars.reserve(128); // e.g. EAN-13 has 96 bars
119#endif
120 for (int x = 0; x < maxLines; x++) {
121
122 // Scanning from the middle out. Determine which row we're looking at next:
123 int rowStepsAboveOrBelow = (x + 1) / 2;
124 bool isAbove = (x & 0x01) == 0; // i.e. is x even?
125 int rowNumber = middle + rowStep * (isAbove ? rowStepsAboveOrBelow : -rowStepsAboveOrBelow);
126 if (rowNumber < 0 || rowNumber >= height) {
127 // Oops, if we run off the top or bottom, stop
128 break;
129 }
130
131#ifdef ZX_USE_NEW_ROW_READERS
132 image.getPatternRow(rowNumber, bars);
133 bool hasBitArray = false;
134#else
135 // Estimate black point for this row and load it:
136 if (!image.getBlackRow(rowNumber, row)) {
137 continue;
138 }
139#endif
140
141 // While we have the image data in a BitArray, it's fairly cheap to reverse it in place to
142 // handle decoding upside down barcodes.
143 // Note: the RSSExpanded decoder depends on seeing each line from both directions. This
144 // 'surprising' and inconsistent. It also requires the decoderState to be shared between
145 // normal and reversed scans, which makes no sense in general because it would mix partial
146 // detetection data from two codes of the same type next to each other. TODO..
147 // See also https://github.com/nu-book/zxing-cpp/issues/87
148 for (bool upsideDown : {false, true}) {
149 // trying again?
150 if (upsideDown) {
151 // reverse the row and continue
152 row.reverse();
153#ifdef ZX_USE_NEW_ROW_READERS
154 std::reverse(bars.begin(), bars.end());
155#endif
156 }
157 // Look for a barcode
158 for (size_t r = 0; r < readers.size(); ++r) {
159#ifdef ZX_USE_NEW_ROW_READERS
160 Result result = readers[r]->decodePattern(rowNumber, bars, decodingState[r]);
161 if (result.status() == DecodeStatus::_internal) {
162 if (!std::exchange(hasBitArray, true)) {
163 row.clearBits();
164 bool set = false;
165 int pos = 0;
166 for(int w : bars) {
167 if (set)
168 for (int i = 0; i < w; ++i)
169 row.set(pos++);
170 else
171 pos += w;
172 set = !set;
173 }
174 }
175 result = readers[r]->decodeRow(rowNumber, row, decodingState[r]);
176 }
177#else
178 Result result = readers[r]->decodeRow(rowNumber, row, decodingState[r]);
179#endif
180 if (result.isValid()) {
181 // We found our barcode
182 if (upsideDown) {
183 // But it was upside down, so note that
184 result.metadata().put(ResultMetadata::ORIENTATION, 180);
185 // And remember to flip the result points horizontally.
186 auto points = result.position();
187 for (auto& p : points) {
188 p = {width - p.x - 1, p.y};
189 }
190 result.setPosition(std::move(points));
191 }
192 return result;
193 }
194 }
195 }
196 }
197 return Result(DecodeStatus::NotFound);
198}
199
200Result
201Reader::decode(const BinaryBitmap& image) const
202{
203 Result result = DoDecode(_readers, image, _tryHarder);
204 if (result.isValid()) {
205 return result;
206 }
207
208 if (_tryRotate && image.canRotate()) {
209 auto rotatedImage = image.rotated(270);
210 result = DoDecode(_readers, *rotatedImage, _tryHarder);
211 if (result.isValid()) {
212 // Record that we found it rotated 90 degrees CCW / 270 degrees CW
213 auto& metadata = result.metadata();
214 metadata.put(ResultMetadata::ORIENTATION, (270 + metadata.getInt(ResultMetadata::ORIENTATION)) % 360);
215 // Update result points
216 auto points = result.position();
217 int height = rotatedImage->height();
218 for (auto& p : points) {
219 p = {height - p.y - 1, p.x};
220 }
221 result.setPosition(std::move(points));
222 }
223 }
224 return result;
225}
